# Regression Test Rule

When a bug is fixed, add a regression test whenever it is reasonably testable.

## Expectations

- Add at least one test that would fail before the fix and pass after it.
- Place the test close to the affected component/module test area.
- Prefer focused unit/integration tests over broad end-to-end coverage.
- If a useful regression test is not feasible, document why in the final reply.

## Verification

- Run the relevant test command(s) after adding/updating regression tests.
- Report what was run and whether it passed or failed.

